        "type": "text",
        "text": "Your **Starfish LED circuit** is ready! ⭐🟠 Here's a full breakdown:\n\n---\n\n## ⭐ Starfish Blinking LED Circuit\n\n### 🐠 Shape Layout\n```\n            💡 Arm 1 (Top)\n           /               \\\n    💡 Arm 5              💡 Arm 2\n          \\     💡 Center  /\n    💡 Arm 4              💡 Arm 3\n           \\               /\n              (bottom)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 🔧 Components\n| Part | Role |\n|------|------|\n| 6x Orange LEDs | 1 Center + 5 Arms of the starfish |\n| 6x 220Ω Resistors | Current limiting for each LED |\n| Arduino Pin 13 | Controls all LEDs simultaneously |\n\n---\n\n### ⚡ How It Works\n- All **6 LEDs share Pin 13** — they all turn ON and OFF together\n- Each LED has its own **220Ω resistor** for safe current limiting\n- The blink pattern:\n  - 🟠 **ON for 700ms** — starfish glows!\n  - ⚫ **OFF for 300ms** — starfish sleeps!\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Blink Pattern\n```\nON  ████████████████████░░░░░░░  repeat...\n    |<--- 700ms glow --->|<300ms>|\n```\n\nThe quick off-flash gives it a **pulse/heartbeat feel** — like a real starfish glowing in the ocean! 🌊"
